1. STEP 85 — Deployment setup (Railway)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1a. Adjust the app to work with Railway's dynamic port assignment:
    Railway injects a PORT environment variable at runtime and expects
    the app to bind to it — it is NOT always 8000. Find wherever
    uvicorn is invoked (likely a Procfile, railway.json, or a run
    command in app/main.py's __main__ block) and change it to read
    the port from os.environ.get("PORT", 8000) and bind host 0.0.0.0.
    If there's no Procfile yet, create one at the project root:
        web: uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
    (Confirm Railway's current expected format for this by checking
    https://docs.railway.com/guides/start-command — Railway has
    supported multiple config methods, verify which one this project
    should use rather than assuming Procfile is still current.)

1b. Adjust persistent storage paths to live under the mounted volume
    (Maj configured this at /data per his manual setup):
    - Wherever the SQLite database path is configured (check
      app/db/database.py or config/settings.py), make it configurable
      via an environment variable (e.g. DATABASE_PATH) defaulting to
      the current relative path for local dev, but settable to
      /data/app.db in Railway's environment variables.
    - Same for the image storage root (data/images/ per step 68) —
      make the base path configurable via an env var (e.g.
      IMAGE_STORAGE_ROOT), defaulting to the current relative path
      locally, settable to /data/images in Railway.
