2c. Add a /health/workers endpoint exposing each worker's last-loop
    heartbeat timestamp. Since there's no server to put a cron job on
    here (unlike the Oracle plan), instead add a lightweight internal
    self-check: have one of the existing worker loops (or a small new
    one) periodically call its own /health/workers endpoint and alert
    via Discord if a heartbeat is stale — this replaces the external
    cron-based health check from the Oracle version, since Railway
    doesn't give you a second always-on place to run a cron script
    without adding a second paid service. Note this tradeoff in the
    changelog: a heartbeat check running inside the same process is
    weaker than an independent external check (if the whole process
    dies, nothing internal can alert), so also confirm Railway's own
    dashboard has crash/restart notifications enabled (Settings →
    Notifications, if available) as a backstop — check what Railway
    actually offers here rather than assuming.

